  "original_title": "Freedom People\u2019s Congress formed to free country of corruption, nepotism and political ignorance",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Freedom People\u2019s Congress formed to free country of corruption, nepotism and political ignorance",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Member Dr. Charitha Herath says country needs broad independent political movement",
        "Claims program would ensure political reforms and politics based on futuristic vision",
        "Sri Lankan Podujana Peramuna (SLPP) MP Dr. Charitha Herath now part of the independent group led by MP Dullas Alahapperuma said Sri Lanka at this juncture needs a broad independent political movement.",
        "According to him, therefore the group\u2019s main objective relating to reforms is to free the country from corruption, nepotism and the making of ignorant political decisions.",
        "The MP made these comments at the opening of a new office by the SLPP independent group titled the \u2018Freedom People\u2019s Congress\u2019 yesterday. The head office of the organisation was declared open by the MPs in Nawala following a simple ceremony consisting of religious and cultural observances.\u00a0 \u00a0\u201cWe are commencing this program to ensure independent reforms and to push the country towards a culture of politics based on talents and a futuristic vision,\u201d he said.",
        "SLPP MPs Dullas Alahapperuma, Dilan Perera, Dr. Nalaka Godahewa, Prof. Charitha Herath, Prof. Channa Jayasumana, K.P.S. Kumarasiri, Dr. Gunapala Rathnasekara, Udayana Kirindigoda, Dr. Upul Galappatti, Dr. Thilak Rajapaksa, Wasantha Yapa, and Lalith Ellawala announced in Parliament this week that they would function as an independent group within the Parliament.",
        "The group also refrained from voting at the interim budget vote held yesterday citing several reasons."
      ],
